    <item>
      <title>Re: Class Issues List - Update</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=shamanbalance&amp;message.id=6072#M6072</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;HR&gt;&#xD;
 &#xD;
&lt;P class=MsoNormal 0in **Zowie**?MARGIN: 0pt?&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P class=MsoNormal 0in **Zowie**?MARGIN: 0pt?&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;FONT size=+0&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;Issue No. 1: Upgrade Shaman Malos Spell Line &lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;SPAN red? **Oompa-Loompa**?COLOR:&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ff0000 size=2&gt;(currently being evaluated) &lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;FONT size=2&gt;Recast delay is unmanageable for the amount debuffed with this single-target spell. Like many core Shaman abilities, it was tuned for a level 65 endgame.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;B&gt;&lt;FONT size=2&gt;Therefore, we propose a new unresistable resist debuff spell in the line, with the standard 2.25 second recast.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/B&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;/BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&#xD;
&lt;HR&gt;&#xD;
&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;FONT size=+0&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;Issue No. 2: Upgrade Shaman Cannibalization AA Line &lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;SPAN red? **Oompa-Loompa**?COLOR:&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;&lt;FONT size=2&gt;(currently being evaluated)&amp;nbsp;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;FONT face="Times New Roman"&gt;&lt;FONT color=#cccccc&gt;&lt;FONT size=3&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;- Most likely this will be considered as part of the class re-envisioning&lt;/FONT&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;FONT size=2&gt;When introduced, Cannibalization was astonishingly powerful, and also quite dicey: it took a lot of the typical shaman's health bar, and as a result there were situations in which it could be used only at significant risk. In return it provided huge amounts of mana, relative to the spells of the day and the mobs of the day. Naturally, spell mana cost has only risen with subsequent expansions and level increases. This ability, once scaled for the level 60 player and spellbook, has fallen behind; it presently is simply an average work tool, returning a modest amount of mana for a modest cost of hp. As a potential solution, please consider the following possibilities:&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;B&gt;&lt;FONT size=2&gt;Improved Cannibalization&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/B&gt;&lt;FONT size=2&gt;: Three ranks, each taking a bigger bite. &lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;B&gt;&lt;FONT size=2&gt;Quickened Cannibalization&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/B&gt;&lt;FONT size=2&gt;: Three ranks, each allowing shorter refresh.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;/BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&lt;/BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&#xD;
&lt;HR&gt;&#xD;
&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;FONT size=+0&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;Issue No. 3: Upgrade Shaman Group Movement Spell &lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;SPAN red? **Oompa-Loompa**?COLOR:&gt;&lt;FONT color=#0066ff size=2&gt;&lt;SPAN red? **Oompa-Loompa**?COLOR:&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;(currently being evaluated)&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;FONT size=2&gt;Shamans are the first class to get SoW (level 9); yet first druids and then rangers get spells that equal and then surpass our ability to buff movement speed. [Spirit of Scale (level 52/53) is pretty fast, but hasn't really been useful since PoK and its books/stones; back in the day that you had to run across ten zones to get somewhere, a movement buff that let you run but not do anything else was still worthwhile; but a no-fight no-cast ability no longer has utility.] That makes Spirit of Bih'li the last upgrade to movement buffs we have received: at level 36. Note that this spell would be a comparable alternative to Flight of Eagles in many situations. As a potential solution, we propose the following new spell:&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;B&gt;&lt;FONT size=2&gt;Spell: Talisman of Bih'Li &lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/B&gt;&lt;FONT size=2&gt;1: See Invisible(2) 2: Increase Movement by 65% 3: Water Breathing(2) 4: Ultravision 6: Increase ATK by 25&lt;/FONT&gt; &lt;FONT size=2&gt;Duration: 1 hour(s) Location: ANY Target Type: Group v2&lt;/FONT&gt; &lt;FONT size=2&gt;Any amount of mana, any level&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;/BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&lt;/BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&#xD;
&lt;HR&gt;&#xD;
&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;FONT size=+0&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;Issue No. 4: Correct Shaman Group Haste Buff &lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;SPAN red? **Oompa-Loompa**?COLOR:&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ff0000 size=2&gt;(currently being evaluated)&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;FONT size=2&gt;We propose that the current spell Talisman of Alacrity be renamed to Talisman of the Wind, and adjusted to be balanced properly. This is not a new spell, but a rewriting of the current version which appears not to be balanced properly. Enchanter group haste spells (Speed of Shissar, Speed of the Brood) remain superior, with 68% haste and valuable melee modifiers. Shamans get to buff to 60% haste at level 63; there is no reason why the group version at the next level should be a downgrade.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;FONT size=2&gt;We propose the following corrections:&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;B&gt;&lt;FONT size=2&gt;Spell: Talisman of the Wind&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/B&gt;&lt;FONT size=2&gt; Group 60% haste (no other stat effects). Duration 36 minutes. Mana cost 750 (3 x Swift like the Wind's 250 mana). Level 64 (one level after shaman single target Swift like the Wind; 17 levels after enchanter single target Swift like the Wind; 4 levels after enchanter group spell Speed of the Brood).&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;/BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&lt;/BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&#xD;
&lt;HR&gt;&#xD;
&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;FONT size=+0&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;Issue No. 5: Improve Shaman Healing &lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;FONT color=#0066ff&gt;&lt;SPAN red? **Oompa-Loompa**?COLOR:&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ff0000 size=2&gt;(currently being evaluated)&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;FONT size=2&gt;In &lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;A href="http://eqlive.station.sony.com/community/dev_view.jsp?id=64032" target=_blank&gt;&lt;FONT color=#fac400 size=2&gt;http://eqlive.station.sony.com/community/dev_view.jsp?id=64032&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/A&gt;&lt;FONT size=2&gt; SOE Developers wrote:&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;FONT size=2&gt;...we are looking to increase your healing ability&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;I&gt;&lt;FONT size=2&gt; &lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/I&gt;&lt;B&gt;&lt;I&gt;&lt;FONT size=2&gt;so you can function better as main healer in groups.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/I&gt;&lt;/B&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;/BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;FONT size=2&gt;As a potential solution, we propose the following new spell:&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;B&gt;&lt;FONT size=2&gt;Spell: Talisman of Trushar&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/B&gt;&lt;FONT size=2&gt; Group Heal over Time. Level 67 (two levels after shaman single target Breath of Trushar). Heals 630 per tick (more than Quiescence, but still well below Spiritual Serenity's 820 per tick) for 4 ticks; the amount healed per tick and buff duration can be increased by standard shaman aa abilities. Mana cost 1260 (3 x Trushar's 420 mana).&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;/BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&lt;/BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&#xD;
&lt;HR&gt;&#xD;
&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;FONT size=+0&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;Issue No. 6: Improve Shaman Survivability &lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;SPAN red? **Oompa-Loompa**?COLOR:&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ff0000 size=2&gt;(currently being evaluated)&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;FONT size=2&gt;As replacement for the current Ancestral Guard AA, we propose the following two AA:&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;B&gt;&lt;FONT size=2&gt;Defense of the Arcane Spirits&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/B&gt;&lt;FONT size=2&gt;: Level 62; 9 aa points. Insta-cast. Reduce the Damage Interval portion of incoming melee damage by 75%, for four ticks (18-24 seconds); duration not extendable by items or aa. Base refresh time: 10 minutes. &lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;B&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;FONT size=2&gt;Quickened Arcane Defense&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/B&gt;&lt;FONT size=2&gt;: Three ranks, Level 66 / 68 / 70; cost 6 / 6 / 6 aa points. Each rank lowers the refresh time of Defense of the Arcane Spirits by 100 seconds.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;/BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;B&gt;&lt;FONT size=2&gt;Background:&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/B&gt;&lt;FONT size=2&gt; Shaman healing is built around the concept: [debuff] / slow / heal. The healing of clerics and druids is built around the concept: heal. Shaman healing is the most difficult of the three priest classes, because it assumes not only that the shaman casts spells on the tank (which might draw aggro), but first must cast spells on the mob (which might draw aggro); moreover, slowing spells are resistable, so they may need to be cast more than once to stick (thus increasing the chance of drawing aggro). Doing all this also takes more time than it takes just to cast healing spells. Melees get a variety of mitigation tools with differing refresh times. Most relevantly, Beastlords get a similar function, Protective Spirit, with a refresh time of 3 min 54 seconds; and Clerics get several emergency functions with refresh times of 3 minutes. The proposed aa length, 4 ticks, is longer by one tick than the druid mitigation buff and some of the cleric effects. That's because the shaman is designed to fill the main healer role through a process that takes time: [debuff] / slow / heal. To address this, the shaman's emergency ability should be at least one tick longer (enough for Turgur's or Nihil, followed by gem refresh). A detailed analysis of this proposal, with comparisons and examples, can be found here. &lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;FONT size=2&gt;The current Ancestral Guard AA is less effective because (1) its short duration means it pretty much has to be clicked at a very precise reactive moment to be effective; (2) as a rune it caps the damage mitigated, instead of (like a discipline) mitigating all damage received during its duration; (3) there is no provision for it to improve as the shaman moves up to harder encounters.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;/BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&#xD;
&lt;HR&gt;&#xD;
&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;FONT size=+0&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;Issue No. 7: Upgrade Shaman Virulent Paralysis AA Line &lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;FONT color=#0066ff&gt;&lt;SPAN red? **Oompa-Loompa**?COLOR:&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ff0000 size=2&gt;(currently being evaluated)&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;FONT size=2&gt;In order to maintain this ability's usefulness, we propose two changes.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;B&gt;&lt;FONT size=2&gt;Improve the resist mod on Virulent Paralysis&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/B&gt;&lt;FONT size=2&gt; In the LDoN era VP3 allowed shamans to do decent improvised crowd control: to knockback one add out of camp while the group dealt with the remaining mob(s). Today's mobs routinely resist and break VP; it needs a better resist mod so that it will land reliably, and generally stick for full duration. &lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;B&gt;&lt;FONT size=2&gt;Add a supplementary AA, Hastened Virulence&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/B&gt;&lt;FONT size=2&gt;: Three ranks, Level 66 / 68 / 70; cost 6 / 6 / 6 aa points. Each rank lowers the refresh time of Virulent Paralysis by 22 seconds.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;FONT size=2&gt; VP3 has a 20 tic duration. This would allow us, at maximum level, to Root-CC two mobs, with VP refreshing at 9 tics.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;/BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&lt;/BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&#xD;
&lt;HR&gt;&#xD;
&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;FONT size=+0&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;Issue No. 8: Improve Shaman DPS &lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;SPAN red? **Oompa-Loompa**?COLOR:&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ff0000 size=2&gt;(currently being evaluated) - Most likely this will be considered as part of the class re-envisioning&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN red? **Oompa-Loompa**?COLOR:&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;FONT size=2&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; We propose three ways that this could be done:&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&#xD;
&lt;BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;B&gt;&lt;FONT size=2&gt;a. Increase the proc a little on the panther / leopard line of buffs &lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/B&gt;&lt;FONT size=2&gt;When implemented, Spirit of Panther was a 550 hp proc, cast on anyone, superproc on pets. This 'first guess' was later judged to be too powerful, and it was severely reduced to the current 400 hp proc, cast within group only, mildly better on pets. We would suggest that this 'second guess' has erred a little too far on the low side, and that panther proc should be increased somewhat, with lower level spells scaled accordingly (the pet proc rate and the in-group restrictions remaining as they presently are). &lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;B&gt;&lt;FONT size=2&gt;b. Implement upper level poison focus items &lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/B&gt;&lt;FONT size=2&gt;There is a noticeable lack of poison focus items at higher levels. Other classes can get the best focus percentages, but there are currently no shaman poison items that correspond to foci obtainable by other classes. &lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;B&gt;&lt;FONT size=2&gt;c. Increase the resist modifiers for shaman damage-over-time spells&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/B&gt;&lt;FONT size=2&gt; &lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;FONT size=2&gt;Other dot classes have large modifiers built into their spells. Sometimes the mobs a group is fighting have their resistances debuffed, and sometimes they don't: but in either case it is common for the shaman spells to bounce while the spells of other classes hit.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;/BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&lt;/BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&#xD;
&lt;HR&gt;&#xD;
&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;FONT size=+0&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;Issue No. 9: Upgrade Shaman Combat Effects Modifier Spells &lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;FONT color=#0066ff&gt;&lt;SPAN red? **Oompa-Loompa**?COLOR:&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ff0000 size=2&gt;(currently being evaluated)&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;FONT size=2&gt;Shaman currently have two spell lines that do not stack in effects (both icons take hold on players, but only one has any benefit), Champion and Spirit/Talisman of Might. In the case of Champion/Talisman, these are both spells we obtain at level 70. In a normal environment, Champion would be cast on our group the entire time, leaving no use for Might. In a raid/group environment, Druids have the exact same effect on their "Lion's Strength" spell as well, leaving minimal use for the spell on a raid. We propose three ways that this could be done:&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;B&gt;&lt;FONT size=2&gt;a. Give Might a "non-melee damage" component to give the spell a use for caster classes.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/B&gt;&lt;FONT size=2&gt; This could be in the form of a stacking focus akin to the bards Rizlona line, or an increase in spell crit chance, or something new and unique. &lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;B&gt;&lt;FONT size=2&gt;b. Allow Champion and Might to stack in effects.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/B&gt;&lt;FONT size=2&gt; &lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;B&gt;&lt;FONT size=2&gt;c. Change the effect on Might to add a bonus to "Combat Effects", Strikethrough, Accuracy,&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/B&gt;&lt;FONT size=2&gt; or something that would be beneficial to our group members.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;/BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&lt;/BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&#xD;
&lt;HR&gt;&#xD;
&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;FONT size=+0&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;Issue No. 10: Upgrade Shaman Bear Form Spell Line &lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;FONT color=#0066ff&gt;&lt;SPAN red? **Oompa-Loompa**?COLOR:&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ff0000 size=2&gt;(currently being evaluated)&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;FONT size=2&gt;Form of the Bear and Form of the Great Bear were popular and useful buffs for shaman leveling up, but we saw them fade from usefulness with no upgrade. The Wisdom boost from Bear is archaic in today's gameplay, as is the token amount of regen. As a potential solution, we propose the following new spell:&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;B&gt;&lt;FONT size=2&gt;Spell: Form of the Oracle &lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/B&gt;&lt;FONT size=2&gt;1: Illusion: Bear 2: Increase Hitpoints by 25 per tick 3: Increase WIS by 25 4: Increase max HP by 500 5: Increase Wis Cap by 25 6: Increase HP when cast by 500&lt;/FONT&gt; &lt;FONT size=2&gt;Duration: 30 minutes or more. Location: ANY Target Type: SELF&lt;/FONT&gt; &lt;FONT size=2&gt;Any level, any mana cost.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;/BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;FONT size=2&gt;This spell would &lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;B&gt;&lt;FONT size=2&gt;not&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/B&gt;&lt;FONT size=2&gt; stack with the Brell/Strength/SV line. The increase in wisdom would be a welcome and unique addition to the class, while keeping in kind with the spirit of the original spell line. The HP regen boost was a staple of the original spell line, and has been modernized for the faster content. The HP boost would help balance it with other class self buffs, while losing the stacking of the paladin line to prevent a large HP gap versus other classes.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;FONT size=2&gt;Note: Community requests that this Bear Form Spell be permitted to stack with the Greater Rabid Bear AA, with one illusion taking precedence.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;/BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&#xD;
&lt;HR&gt;&#xD;
&lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
